2026-04-08 | Apply Queries with Step Updates and Return XOR

	Question
Apply all updates and return final XOR of array.

	Approach
1.	Loop through each query:
2.	For each query:
		for idx = li to ri step ki:
			update nums[idx]

3.	After all queries:
		compute XOR of array  

4.	Use MOD = 1e9 + 7  

	Time Complexity
	Worst case: O(q × n/ki) → O(qn)  

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int processQueries(vector<int>& nums, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {

        const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;

        for(auto &q : queries){

            int l = q[0];
            int r = q[1];
            int k = q[2];
            int v = q[3];

            for(int idx = l; idx <= r; idx += k){
                nums[idx] = (1LL * nums[idx] * v) % MOD;
            }
        }

        int ans = 0;

        for(int x : nums){
            ans ^= x;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Each query updates only **specific indices with step k**.  

Since constraints usually allow it, direct simulation works.  
Finally, XOR aggregation gives the result efficiently.
